case_circumstances: The remains consist of a human foot found in a boot in shallow water on the west shoreline of American Lake, Fort Lewis, WA.  Searches of the lake conducted by boat and by scuba teams for additional evidence and additional remains met with negative results. The boot appeared to have been in the water for some time due to the large amounts of algae covering its surface.  The remains were estimated by the medical examiner to have been submerged for about 1-2 years.
fingerprints: Fingerprint information is currently not available
case_footwear: The boot was a black leather military combat boot, size 11-R.  A green and cotton type sock was inside the boot.
dental: Dental information / charting is currently not available
documents: There are currently no documents available for this case.
